{"key":"processedPost-12163230","value":{"id":12163230,"first":12163114,"last":12176045,"when":1268058985,"utime":"03/08/10 04:36 PM","content":"Rye grass seed and rye berries are from two different plants.&nbsp; Rye berries ARE for cooking, or planting rye grain.&nbsp; Rye grass seed is for planting a lawn.&nbsp; Both will work for fungi, but I prefer rye berries.&nbsp; Incidentally, rye berries are better for sclerotia producing species than grass seed, and if one chooses to use grass seed, it need not be rye grass.&nbsp; Every type I've tried has worked just fine.<br />RR","title":"Re: Organic Rye berries?"}}